Effective Date: February 14, 2026
Last Updated: February 14, 2026

1. Information We Process
This extension only processes data when you actively start OCR by selecting an area on a webpage. Data may include:

Image content within the area you selected (for OCR only)
Recognized text result
Local settings and latest OCR result stored in your browser
2. How We Use Information
Processed data is used only to:

Run OCR for selected on-screen content
Show OCR results to you
Copy OCR results to your clipboard
Save the latest result locally for your convenience
3. Storage and Data Transfer
OCR is performed locally by default.
We do not intentionally send your screenshots or recognized text to our own servers.
If Tesseract is enabled, language files (for example, eng) may be downloaded from a public model host on first use and then cached by your browser.
4. Permissions We Request
activeTab / scripting: inject selection and OCR logic into the active page
tabs: identify active tab and perform capture flow
clipboardWrite: copy recognized text to clipboard
storage: store latest OCR result locally
host_permissions: <all_urls>: allow OCR selection on pages you choose to use
5. Third-Party Components
This extension may use third-party OCR components (such as Tesseract.js) and public language model hosting.
Your OCR content is not intentionally shared with third parties; external requests are limited to loading model assets when needed.

6. Data Retention and Deletion
OCR results saved by this extension are stored locally in your browser.
You can remove stored data at any time by clearing extension storage or uninstalling the extension.
7. Children’s Privacy
This extension is not directed to children under 13.

8. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be reflected in the extension listing or release notes.

9. Contact
For privacy-related questions, contact us via the contact method listed on the extension’s store page.
